FBIS4-5055 "dreas067_a_94018" FBIS-EAS-94-067 Daily Report 7 Apr 1994 NORTHEAST ASIA Japan Bills To Relax Car Inspection Rules Announced Bills To Relax Car Inspection Rules Announced OW0704130394 Tokyo KYODO in English 1207 GMT 7 Apr 94 OW0704130394 Tokyo KYODO English BFN [Text] Tokyo, April 7 KYODO -- The Transport Ministry on Thursday [7 April] announced bills to relax car inspection regulations as part of government deregulation efforts. The deregulation involves the elimination of rules requiring a car inspection once every six months as well as a reduction in items required for annual and biennial car inspections. The ministry plans to implement the latest measures next year, ministry officials said. The ministry expects the scrapping of the six-month inspection requirements to save car owners an average 15,000 yen and the reduction in items for annual and biennial inspections to save them 4,000 yen and 8,000 yen, respectively, they said.
